      "file_path": "openecomp-be/lib/openecomp-sdc-translator-lib/openecomp-sdc-translator-core/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/translator/services/heattotosca/TranslationService.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 240,
      "message": "If the condition is met, the method returns without ever using the variables declared and allocated above. It's a best practice to declare variables and instantiate object only when you need them, right before you need them.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2017-10-03 07:17:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9a437d4f_2ba219fd",
      "file_path": "openecomp-be/lib/openecomp-sdc-translator-lib/openecomp-sdc-translator-core/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/translator/services/heattotosca/TranslationService.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 241,
      "message": "Don't create empty collections if you're not going to populate them. Use Collections.emptySet()/emptyMap() etc. It is more efficient and immutable, so you will know if you try to put something into it by mistake.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2017-10-03 07:17:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
